    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi ! \n\nThanks for the PR ! \n\nMy personal opinion on this one would be to maybe have an explicit end of cell (for example an `%%end` cell magic). I don't have searched for argument for or against an implicit delimiter (`\\n\\n`) or an explicit delimiter though.\n\nI think we should think of how are handled nesteed magic.\nwould `%%timeit` wrapping `%%bash` require 4 newline ?\n\nAnd also how much user are used to skip line and will inadvertently break the cell.\n\nDoes `\\n\\n`have special meaning in other potential languages (LaTeX processing ? Coffeescript?)\n\nAlso, If we have a strict marker at the end, would it be possible to indent for readability ?\n\nThanks ! \n"
  },
